    "name": "Farm-to-Table • Plate Templates Catalog",
    "label": "Plate Templates",
    "subtitle": "Deterministic plate-model templates used by planners to assemble balanced meals using farm-to-table components and roles.",
    "source": {
      "kind": "catalog",
      "name": "src/catalogs/farm-to-table/plate_templates.catalog.json",
      "notes": [
        "Templates define roles, required slots, and common pairings; planners resolve to actual components via inventory, cuisine rulesets, and substitutions.",
        "Portioning is expressed as flexible hints (not strict nutrition). Nutrition modules can override with macro targets.",
        "Use plannerTags to bias search (weeknight/batch/leftovers/etc.)."
      ]
    }
  },
